      "content": "thanks. so i'm thinking about how this guide might be received in places like southeast asia or west africa. the \"standard\" you described—the suits and the specific dinner etiquette—definitely works in london or nyc, but how would you frame those traditional customs in those regions in the guide? like, do we include them as part of the professional standard, or should we just list them as \"cultural exceptions\" to keep the main guide clean?",
